1
00:00:00,599 --> 00:00:06,310
Price action is the simplest and easiest form
of reading and analyzing a market.

2
00:00:06,310 --> 00:00:12,309
But the problem is that many traders are complicating
their process, and analyze things on the chart

3
00:00:12,309 --> 00:00:14,400
that are irrelevant.

4
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:19,949
Let me show you an easy method to read price
action, without needing to memorize dozens

5
00:00:19,949 --> 00:00:24,699
of candlesticks or stare at the charts for
hours to find patterns.

6
00:00:24,699 --> 00:00:31,180
You know the drill: like, subscribe, and stick
around for the full video.

7
00:00:31,180 --> 00:00:35,890
TREND BARS

8
00:00:35,890 --> 00:00:40,730
The first thing you should look for when you
are analyzing a chart, is the spread of recent

9
00:00:40,730 --> 00:00:42,070
candles.

10
00:00:42,070 --> 00:00:48,120
The spread is the difference between a candle’s
open and its close (this is the real body

11
00:00:48,120 --> 00:00:49,820
of the candle).

12
00:00:49,820 --> 00:00:52,960
The spread reveals the sentiment for that
candle.

13
00:00:52,960 --> 00:00:58,510
A wide spread between the open and the close
indicates strong market sentiment, either

14
00:00:58,510 --> 00:01:04,409
bullish or bearish, depending on whether the
closing price finished above the opening price

15
00:01:04,409 --> 00:01:05,640
or below it.

16
00:01:05,640 --> 00:01:12,580
And if the body of the candle takes up at
least 50% of the entire bar range, then you

17
00:01:12,580 --> 00:01:15,259
are seeing a trend Bar.

18
00:01:15,259 --> 00:01:19,150
Trend bars represent the meat of the market
fluctuations.

19
00:01:19,150 --> 00:01:22,110
The concept of Trend Bars is very simple.

20
00:01:22,110 --> 00:01:28,259
Price action simply creates a solid candle
with small wicks at the top or the bottom,

21
00:01:28,259 --> 00:01:34,399
and is suggesting a strong and a likely continued
sentiment in the direction of the candle.

22
00:01:34,399 --> 00:01:41,220
A trend candle represents strong market sentiment
and a narrow spread one shows a weak market

23
00:01:41,220 --> 00:01:44,450
sentiment.

24
00:01:44,450 --> 00:01:51,180
If we analyze this chart, between these two
points, there were no instances of consecutive

25
00:01:51,180 --> 00:01:54,840
Trend Bars that closed in the same direction.

26
00:01:54,840 --> 00:01:59,960
We had several Trend Bars, but they were isolated
instances.

27
00:01:59,960 --> 00:02:06,049
When we had consecutive Trend Bars, they actually
closed in opposing directions.

28
00:02:06,049 --> 00:02:09,500
Here we see consecutive bullish Trend Bars.

29
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:12,160
It shows evident bullish strength.

30
00:02:12,160 --> 00:02:18,860
Very important: when the trend is strong,
you’ll see many trend bars in the direction

31
00:02:18,860 --> 00:02:19,860
of the trend.

32
00:02:19,860 --> 00:02:26,180
And, if there are no Trend Bars for the past
ten bars, for example, then the market is

33
00:02:26,180 --> 00:02:29,500
likely consolidating.

34
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:37,680
LONG SHADOWS
The upper and lower wicks of candlesticks

35
00:02:37,680 --> 00:02:42,030
reflect the buying and selling pressure.

36
00:02:42,030 --> 00:02:47,230
Consider wicks as ‘rejection’ areas where
the market simply rejected the prices of the

37
00:02:47,230 --> 00:02:48,879
wick.

38
00:02:48,879 --> 00:02:54,810
When you see a wick that is large, that wick
is clearly telling you that the market was

39
00:02:54,810 --> 00:02:58,629
not accepting the previous prices.

40
00:02:58,629 --> 00:03:02,610
Time frame is important here and we’ll talk
about this later.

41
00:03:02,610 --> 00:03:08,450
If you are trading on the 5min charts, then
the market has rejected that price level with

42
00:03:08,450 --> 00:03:14,250
that wick, but for only the past 5 minutes,
which is not that significant.

43
00:03:14,250 --> 00:03:22,470
However, when you start to look at 4hr or
daily charts, that wick is more significant.

44
00:03:22,470 --> 00:03:27,460
The length of any wick, either to the top
or bottom of the candle is ALWAYS the first

45
00:03:27,460 --> 00:03:34,850
point of focus because it instantly shows,
strength, weakness, or indecision, and most

46
00:03:34,850 --> 00:03:39,140
important where buyers or sellers are entering
the market.

47
00:03:39,140 --> 00:03:45,930
In fact, the wick itself is not important,
the price level at which the wick occurred

48
00:03:45,930 --> 00:03:49,620
is what matters.

49
00:03:49,620 --> 00:03:55,489
Taking a look at this chart, notice how every
time the market reversed, it did so with a

50
00:03:55,489 --> 00:04:00,800
large wick and almost at the same price level.

51
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:06,840
This is telling you the market simply did
not accept prices at these levels, with sellers

52
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:12,030
aggressively entering the market quickly,
causing the price to drop faster.

53
00:04:12,030 --> 00:04:18,540
CONSECUTIVE BARS CLOSING IN THE SAME DIRECTION

54
00:04:18,540 --> 00:04:24,919
So, when you analyze a chart, you start by
paying more attention to trend bars and bars

55
00:04:24,919 --> 00:04:26,050
with long shadows.

56
00:04:26,050 --> 00:04:32,259
Now, in a market, there are trends at various
levels.

57
00:04:32,259 --> 00:04:38,300
Consecutive bars closing in the same direction
is one of the easiest ways to identify minor

58
00:04:38,300 --> 00:04:39,750
trends.

59
00:04:39,750 --> 00:04:42,650
The number of successive bars matters too.

60
00:04:42,650 --> 00:04:45,660
The more, the better.

61
00:04:45,660 --> 00:04:52,009
When you have consecutive trend bars in the
same direction, you have lots of momentum.

62
00:04:52,009 --> 00:05:00,310
In many cases, consecutive price bars will
help you to identify sustained price movements.

63
00:05:00,310 --> 00:05:05,333
OVERLAP WITH THE PREVIOUS BAR

64
00:05:05,333 --> 00:05:11,000
The degree of overlap with the previous bar
tells you the current market phase and the

65
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:13,990
power of the price bar.

66
00:05:13,990 --> 00:05:20,880
In a strong trend, there is very little overlap
of the bodies of consecutive bars.

67
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:30,009
For example, in a minor uptrend, many candles
have lows that are at or just below the closes

68
00:05:30,009 --> 00:05:32,730
of the prior candles.

69
00:05:32,730 --> 00:05:38,949
Some candles don’t even test the close of
the prior bar, and traders trying to enter

70
00:05:38,949 --> 00:05:44,650
with a limit order at the close of the prior
bar won’t get their orders filled, so they

71
00:05:44,650 --> 00:05:47,419
have to buy higher.

72
00:05:47,419 --> 00:05:53,740
The point is, if you find minimal overlap
between a candle and the preceding one, it

73
00:05:53,740 --> 00:05:55,000
implies urgency.

74
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:58,009
And start paying more attention to this.

75
00:05:58,009 --> 00:06:05,280
Again, in this bearish down move, many bars
have highs that are at or just above the closes

76
00:06:05,280 --> 00:06:07,270
of the prior bar.

77
00:06:07,270 --> 00:06:13,889
This shows strength and it’s an important
sign because the market is unable to go higher

78
00:06:13,889 --> 00:06:17,840
and it keeps pushing lower.

79
00:06:17,840 --> 00:06:24,280
So if no wick or a very small wick is created,
then this signals strong market sentiment

80
00:06:24,280 --> 00:06:27,639
in the direction of the closing price.

81
00:06:27,639 --> 00:06:30,430
It indicates urgency in the market.

82
00:06:30,430 --> 00:06:36,479
If the bar you are looking at overlaps entirely
with the previous bar, the market doesn’t

83
00:06:36,479 --> 00:06:39,120
have the greatest momentum.

84
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:41,860
This is especially true with inside bars.

85
00:06:41,860 --> 00:06:47,580
Inside bar are smaller and within the range
of the prior bar.

86
00:06:47,580 --> 00:06:54,729
100% overlap bars and consecutive candles
that are overlapping are a clear sign of market

87
00:06:54,729 --> 00:06:55,729
congestion.

88
00:06:55,729 --> 00:07:02,730
Wicks below bullish bars and above bearish
bars

89
00:07:02,730 --> 00:07:08,099
In a strong uptrend, you will see wicks below
the bullish bars.

90
00:07:08,099 --> 00:07:13,509
This represents a good signal that the buyers
are in control of the market and that are

91
00:07:13,509 --> 00:07:17,600
trying to push the prices upwards.

92
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:23,680
You will also see wicks above the bearish
bars in a strong downtrend.

93
00:07:23,680 --> 00:07:29,349
This shows that the sellers are in control
and that are successfully pushing the prices

94
00:07:29,349 --> 00:07:30,349
downwards.

95
00:07:30,349 --> 00:07:39,960
REACTION AFTER A TEST OF SUPPORT/RESISTANCE
Pay more attention to candlesticks that test

96
00:07:39,960 --> 00:07:43,180
any support/resistance areas.

97
00:07:43,180 --> 00:07:48,550
You may find that the candle has difficulty
breaking through the level.

98
00:07:48,550 --> 00:07:55,409
Or you may find that the candle completely
ignores the level and breaks it with ease.

99
00:07:55,409 --> 00:08:00,120
In either case, they help you to formulate
a trading approach.

100
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:06,919
If we look at the recent price action, I see
a test of this support level, which resulted

101
00:08:06,919 --> 00:08:09,039
in a bullish Pin Bar.

102
00:08:09,039 --> 00:08:15,740
As I said before, a long shadow implies bullish
pressure.

103
00:08:15,740 --> 00:08:23,069
On the other hand, the market completely ignored
this resistance level and broke above it decisively.

104
00:08:23,069 --> 00:08:32,279
No retest of previous breakouts
So let’s assume that price broke a significant

105
00:08:32,279 --> 00:08:33,279
resistance level.

106
00:08:33,279 --> 00:08:39,000
And of course, all trading manuals say that
in order to trade a breakout, you must wait

107
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:42,269
for price to re-test the breakout level.

108
00:08:42,269 --> 00:08:48,380
But, very important, in a strong market, you
will not get a retest.

109
00:08:48,380 --> 00:08:53,080
The buyers are unwilling to let the price
drop lower.

110
00:08:53,080 --> 00:09:00,610
There is little profit taking after the breakout,
so price won’t come to retest the breakout

111
00:09:00,610 --> 00:09:02,680
level.

112
00:09:02,680 --> 00:09:09,370
So when you see an important level, and price
breaks it, and has strong upward momentum,

113
00:09:09,370 --> 00:09:16,430
without re-testing the level, there’s again
a sense of urgency, a higher volatility and

114
00:09:16,430 --> 00:09:19,300
high momentum.

115
00:09:19,300 --> 00:09:26,581
TOP-DOWN ANALYSIS
When you’re reading price action, analyzing

116
00:09:26,581 --> 00:09:32,700
only the 15 min chart, for example, won’t
bring you consistency in the longer term.

117
00:09:32,700 --> 00:09:34,730
You need more information.

118
00:09:34,730 --> 00:09:40,140
When a particular timeframe DON’T make sense,
then move to the next higher time frame, at

119
00:09:40,140 --> 00:09:49,330
least, for the big picture or even on a lower
timeframe for the microstructure of move.

120
00:09:49,330 --> 00:09:54,390
When you’re trading price action, you need
a top-down analysis, which is a more efficient

121
00:09:54,390 --> 00:09:56,830
and effective way to trade.

122
00:09:56,830 --> 00:10:03,579
A simple top-down approach means marking out
the support and resistance first on higher

123
00:10:03,579 --> 00:10:05,750
time frames.

124
00:10:05,750 --> 00:10:10,820
Then you read price action of the higher time
frames, and see what the price is telling

125
00:10:10,820 --> 00:10:13,990
you and where it may be heading.

126
00:10:13,990 --> 00:10:20,610
Then, with that market structure in mind,
zoom into the lower-level details.

127
00:10:20,610 --> 00:10:27,890
Context of the price move

128
00:10:27,890 --> 00:10:35,320
Now, reading price action is not about finding
pin bars, engulfing patterns, or seeing if

129
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:38,440
there are more green candles than red ones.

130
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:44,610
It is about observing price bars as they form
and understanding what the market has done

131
00:10:44,610 --> 00:10:46,050
and is doing.

132
00:10:46,050 --> 00:10:52,519
A candle of the same type will have a completely
different meaning depending on where it appears

133
00:10:52,519 --> 00:10:54,520
in a price trend.

134
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:59,810
• Is it at a start of trend or in the middle
of the trend or end of it.

135
00:10:59,810 --> 00:11:08,240
• Is it at support or resistance or in the
middle of a consolidation phase.

136
00:11:08,240 --> 00:11:11,800
Candlesticks should be analyzed in the context
of the price move.

137
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:16,560
You should never try and read the candle in
isolation.

138
00:11:16,560 --> 00:11:24,110
Analyzing multiple bars as a group, on several
time frames offers a lot more analytical value.

139
00:11:24,110 --> 00:11:26,700
Here we have 2 similar pin bars.

140
00:11:26,700 --> 00:11:30,310
But this one is the more important.

141
00:11:30,310 --> 00:11:39,040
It appeared in the context of an uptrend,
with multiple trend bars at a support level.

142
00:11:39,040 --> 00:11:46,750
While this one appeared after many candles
are overlapping, so in a congestion area.

143
00:11:46,750 --> 00:11:52,990
The point is: start reading the current candle
in relation to the previous bars.

144
00:11:52,990 --> 00:11:57,620
• Is the current candlestick larger or smaller
than previous ones?

145
00:11:57,620 --> 00:12:02,040
• Which recent candles are showing momentum
increases or decreases

146
00:12:02,040 --> 00:12:06,110
• Is the size of the body meaningful or
not?

147
00:12:06,110 --> 00:12:08,420
• Are you seeing buying or selling pressure

148
00:12:08,420 --> 00:12:18,329
Volume validates price
Price goes hand in hand with volume.

149
00:12:18,329 --> 00:12:22,600
Is it possible to make money trading using
price action alone?

150
00:12:22,600 --> 00:12:23,600
Sure.

151
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:28,070
But price in combination with volume is 10
times better.

152
00:12:28,070 --> 00:12:34,380
First, you see what the CANDLESTICK is telling
you, then you check the volume, and see if

153
00:12:34,380 --> 00:12:38,700
it’s validating or not with the recent price
action.

154
00:12:38,700 --> 00:12:40,000
Volume validates price.

155
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:46,200
It’s the fuel that drives the market, and
the more fuel there is, the greater the market

156
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:49,000
momentum.

157
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:55,240
Volume confirms the strength of a candlestick
or suggests its weakness.

158
00:12:55,240 --> 00:13:01,430
If the market is rising with a trend bar,
and we have volume which is increasing, then

159
00:13:01,430 --> 00:13:07,140
this suggests that we have a strong price
move supported by an increasing number of

160
00:13:07,140 --> 00:13:08,920
buyers.

161
00:13:08,920 --> 00:13:16,010
This is BUYING volume, and you expect the
price move to continue in this case.

162
00:13:16,010 --> 00:13:23,020
If you have a trend bar, but you see decreasing
volume, then this is WEAK price move.

163
00:13:23,020 --> 00:13:29,199
If strong buyers were still in the market,
then this would be represented by RISING volume,

164
00:13:29,199 --> 00:13:35,170
and in this case we have FALLING volume, so
this is a warning sign that the buyers are

165
00:13:35,170 --> 00:13:37,139
NO LONGER INTERESTED.

166
00:13:37,139 --> 00:13:40,079
The trend may be running out of steam.

167
00:13:40,079 --> 00:13:44,540
This is the first sign of a POSSIBLE change
in trend.

168
00:13:44,540 --> 00:13:49,731
Combining Volume and Price

169
00:13:49,731 --> 00:13:55,180
Price alone can only tell you what a market’s
present technical position really is, and

170
00:13:55,180 --> 00:13:58,670
where the trend is probably headed.

171
00:13:58,670 --> 00:14:05,290
Volume help to validate the trend with more
accuracy and also detects turning points,

172
00:14:05,290 --> 00:14:08,180
when to open or close trades.

173
00:14:08,180 --> 00:14:10,980
And together, they form a complete picture.

174
00:14:10,980 --> 00:14:17,029
I’ve talked about the Volume spread analysis
in this video, and if you haven’t seen it

175
00:14:17,029 --> 00:14:20,310
yet, this must be your next video to watch.

176
00:14:20,310 --> 00:14:26,880
VSA seeks to establish the cause of price
movements by considering the imbalance between

177
00:14:26,880 --> 00:14:28,899
buying and selling.

178
00:14:28,899 --> 00:14:35,570
If you think about it, volume expresses interest
and enthusiasm in one simple bar.

179
00:14:35,570 --> 00:14:42,399
All the buying and selling decisions of investors,
retail traders and smart money are all contained

180
00:14:42,399 --> 00:14:44,860
in one volume bar.

181
00:14:44,860 --> 00:14:50,699
All the millions of trading decisions, whether
to buy or to sell are all captured in this

182
00:14:50,699 --> 00:14:53,500
one bar.

183
00:14:53,500 --> 00:14:56,690
Volume exposes the truth of a candlestick.

184
00:14:56,690 --> 00:14:59,709
It reveals the conviction in the recent price
move.

185
00:14:59,709 --> 00:15:06,110
If the market is moving higher, but with falling
or low volume, then this is simply telling

186
00:15:06,110 --> 00:15:09,459
you that this is not a genuine move.

187
00:15:09,459 --> 00:15:16,120
Equally, if the market is decreasing with
falling volume, then once again this is not

188
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:18,740
a genuine move.

189
00:15:18,740 --> 00:15:26,910
The more volume associated with a price move,
then the more that price move is validated.

190
00:15:26,910 --> 00:15:34,019
When there is low volume, few sellers in this
example, then this price may simply not be

191
00:15:34,019 --> 00:15:36,040
validated.

192
00:15:36,040 --> 00:15:42,670
But when we have many sellers, this will reflect
in high volume, and then our price is validated.

193
00:15:42,670 --> 00:15:46,240
It really is that simple.

194
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:51,690
I hope that you can start to see how volume
and price are the only two aspects of a chart

195
00:15:51,690 --> 00:15:53,260
that you need to understand.

196
00:15:53,260 --> 00:15:58,880
Learn how these work together, and you will
join the elite group of traders who have the

197
00:15:58,880 --> 00:16:04,290
ability to literally “read the market”
and are able to anticipate where price is

198
00:16:04,290 --> 00:16:08,420
likely to be heading, before it happens.

199
